# Rust
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Environment
.env
.env.local

# Database
*.db
# SQLite sidecars (WAL + shared-memory). These MUST NOT be versioned:
# SQLite treats sparks.db, sparks.db-wal, sparks.db-shm as a single atomic
# unit. Tracking the sidecars while .ryve/sparks.db is ignored produces
# torn state on stash/checkout and corrupts the workgraph. See
# docs/WORKGRAPH.md (Sidecars must never be tracked).
.ryve/sparks.db
.ryve/sparks.db-*
**/worktrees/

# Vendored tmux build output (built locally via scripts/build-vendored-tmux.sh)
vendor/tmux/bin/

# Vendored ngIRCd build output (built locally via scripts/build-vendored-ircd.sh)
vendor/ircd/bin/

# Ryve runtime artifacts (per-Hand prompts and logs)
.ryve/prompts/
.ryve/logs/

# Per-workshop runtime config + UI state. These are user-specific
# (often contain secrets — GitHub PATs, webhook secrets, IRC passwords)
# and machine-specific (port allocations, layout dimensions, collapsed
# spark IDs). Tracking them produces both privacy leaks and merge
# churn. `ryve init` creates a fresh config.toml on first launch;
# ui_state.json is recreated by the app.
.ryve/config.toml
.ryve/ui_state.json
.ryve/ircd/

# Claude Code session lock — runtime, contains live session ID + PID.
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock